Interface Statement


  • public interface Statement
    Provides methods for setting values for precompiled SQL statements and executing precompiled SQL statements.

      • setObject

        void setObject​(int index,
               Object value)
        Sets an object value for a precompiled statement dynamically.

        The method used to set the value varies depending on the value type:

        • If the value is null, use Statement#setNull(int).
        • If the value type is Boolean, use Statement#setLong(int, long). 1 indicates true and 0 indicates false.
        • If the value type is byte array, use Statement#setBlob(int, byte[]).
        • If the value type is Double or Float, use Statement#setDouble(int, double).
        • If the value type is Number, use Statement#setLong(int, long).

        If the value is not any of the preceding types, convert it into a string and use Statement#setString(int, String) to set it.

        Parameters:
        index - Indicates the index of the value to be set for the precompiled statement, which starts from 1.
        value - Indicates the value to be set for the precompiled statement.
        Since:
        1
